    'help_plugins_content' => '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #333333; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;margin-top: 0.5em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.8em; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;Plugin Parameter&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;amp;plugin=`thumb: pluginName1#prerender, pluginName2 | gallery: pluginName3, pluginName4@custom/index/file.php | landingpage: pluginName5`&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;Originally, plugins only make a new layer above the thumbnail.&lt;br /&gt;But in the displaying process, each of plugin gets all thumbnails&#039; information from the database by their IDs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;All IDs of files are identified by&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;fid_&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;[file_id]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;All IDs of directories are identified by&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;gid_&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;[gallery_id]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;ID for the landingpage is identified by&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;fid_&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;[file_id]&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;The plugins target the specified objects:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 20px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 10px; font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 5px; list-style-type: disc; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: url(media/style/MODxCarbon/images/misc/li.gif); margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;thumb (for image thumbnail),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 5px; list-style-type: disc; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: url(media/style/MODxCarbon/images/misc/li.gif); margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;gallery (for directory thumbnail),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 5px; list-style-type: disc; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: url(media/style/MODxCarbon/images/misc/li.gif); margin: 0px;&quot;&gt;and landingpage (for the image in the landing page).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;If the snippet calls more than one target, the pipe symbol ( | ) is used as delimiter of each of target.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;The target call is followed by plugin&#039;s name after a colon, which are separated by comma if there are more than one plugin applied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;The plugin&#039;s name is followed by a path to a customized index file after an @ (ampersand) sign, if there is any.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: normal; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;The # (hash) symbol is to targeting the &#039;prerender&#039; or &#039;render&#039; on event process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;',
